name: Exoskeleton restrained (with anatomical issues)
description:
Add pointy ears to negatives to prevent elven ears. You may try these tags: mechanical arms, mechanical legs, arms behind back, bound arms, reverse pray, extra arms, four arms, extra legs, four legs but they may wont work as intended.

Fake mechanical limbs while the real ones are immobilized.

A very early version that I tried over a month ago, but failed due to a lack of images or improperly spelled tags. A total of 16 attempts and over 120,000 training steps were spoiled. I'm posting some more or less successful models that didn't turn faces into mess. I gave up and won't be able to go back to it anytime soon, so I decided to post it as is.

I guess the only way to make such a model is to generate yourself in a 3d editor (daz, mmd, blender, even sfm) enough material. I don't have the next few months such an opportunity
